# How to provision an EC2 instance at amazonaws.com
AWS Console
- EC2
  - Launch Instance
    - Choose Amazon Machine Image
      - Red Hat Enterprise Linux 8 (HVM)
        - t2.small, 2GB Memory
        - Next: Configure Instances
        - Next: Add Storage
        - Next: Add tags
         - Add Tag - Key: Name Value: RHEL EC2 Instance
        - Next: Configure Security Group
          - Assign a Security Group
            - Create a new security group
              - Security group name: RedHatSecurityGroup
              - Description: Red Hat Security Group

        - Port Range 22 > Source > My IP
        - Add Rule > Port Range > 8081
  - Review and Launch
  - Launch
    - Create a new key pair
    - Key pair name > $KEY_PAIR_NAME
  - Download Key Pair
  - Launch Instances

# at command line
chmod 400 $KEY_PAIR_NAME.pem
ssh -i $KEY_PAIR_NAME.pem ec2-user@$EC2_INSTANCE_PUBLIC_IP
sudo yum -y update
